trans-unit.source: Represents a single user interface (UI) entity managed by an <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Adorner" />.
trans-unit.target: Reprezentuje jednostkę interfejsu pojedynczego użytkownika zarządza <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Adorner" />.

trans-unit.source: The sole purpose of a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> is to paint and hit test.
trans-unit.target: Wyłącznie do celów <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> jest do rysowania i testowania trafienia.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> does not have a window handle (HWND), as it is rendered on the adorner window control of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.
trans-unit.target: A <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> nie ma uchwyt okna (HWND), ponieważ jest on renderowany na moduł definiowania układu okna kontroli <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.

trans-unit.source: Each <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> can have a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> associated with it.
trans-unit.target: Każdy <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> może mieć <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> skojarzonych z nim.

trans-unit.source: A successfully hit-tested <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> has the opportunity to push a new or different <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> onto the behavior stack of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.
trans-unit.target: Pomyślnie trafień badania <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> ma możliwość push nowy lub innych <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Behavior> na stosie zachowanie <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService>.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Behavior Service Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7c60cc41-4324-46b5-b444-b39eda7cb33f).
trans-unit.target: Aby uzyskać więcej informacji, zobacz [Omówienie usługi zachowanie](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7c60cc41-4324-46b5-b444-b39eda7cb33f).

trans-unit.target: Wskaż trafień testu.

trans-unit.source: Provides hit test logic.
trans-unit.target: Zawiera logikę testu trafienia.

trans-unit.source: A <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor" /> if the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph" /> is associated with <paramref name="p" />; otherwise, <see langword="null" />.
trans-unit.target: A <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor" /> Jeśli <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph" /> jest skojarzony z <paramref name="p" />; w przeciwnym razie <see langword="null" />.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph.GetHitTest%2A> method is an `abstract` method that forces <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> implementations to provide hit test logic.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph.GetHitTest%2A> Jest metoda `abstract` — metoda, która wymusza <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> implementacji, aby zapewnić logikę testu trafienia.

trans-unit.source: Given any point, if the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> has decided to be involved with that location, it will need to return a valid <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor>.
trans-unit.target: Podane dowolnego punktu, jeśli <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.Glyph> postanowiła związane z czy lokalizacji, trzeba będzie zwracać prawidłowy <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Cursor>.

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, returning `null` will cause the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService> to ignore the location.
trans-unit.target: W przeciwnym razie zwraca `null` spowoduje, że <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.Behavior.BehaviorService> zignorowanie lokalizacji.
